To create an actor instance with a parameter, you can modify the constructor of the actor class to accept parameters. For example, in Python, you can modify the Counter class like this:

@ray.remote
class Counter:
    def __init__(self, start_value):
        self.value = start_value

    def increment(self):
        self.value += 1
        return self.value

    def get_counter(self):
        return self.value

# Create an actor from this class with a start value of 5.
counter = Counter.remote(5)

This will create an instance of the Counter actor with a starting value of 5. Similar modifications can be made for Java and C++.

